text: The Collective Security Treaty Organization (CSTO; ; ) is a government military alliance in Eurasia. Its members of some post-Soviet states. The treaty was inspired by the Soviet Armed Forces. On 15 May 1992, six post- Soviet states belonging to the Commonwealth of Independent States, Russia, Armenia, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, Tajikistan, and Uzbekistan, signed the Collective Security Treaty. ==Notes== ==References== Category:1992 establishments in Russia Category:1990s establishments in Kazakhstan Category:1990s establishments in Kyrgyzstan Category:1992 establishments in Armenia Category:History of Uzbekistan Category:History of Tajikistan
